{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7df4227-6c76-41ee-818e-9efb0cabb6c3","content":"There are no files in the working directory, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML page root:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only structural change** is adding `xmlns:vm` and `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` to the `<ContentPage>`. All `{Binding …}` expressions stay the same — the XAML compiler now resolves them at build time against `SettingsViewModel`.\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\n**2. Enable strict mode** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Turns binding mismatches into compile errors (not just warnings) -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith this enabled, if you typo a property (e.g., `{Binding Fonsize}`), the build **fails** with an error like:\n\n```\nXC0045: Binding: Property \"Fonsize\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n```\n\n**Key rules to remember:**\n\n| Scenario | What to do |\n|---|---|\n| Binding targets a different type mid-tree (e.g., inside a `DataTemplate`) | Add a new `x:DataType` on that element |\n| Need to opt out for one binding (e.g., `RelativeSource`) | Use `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"` locally |\n| ViewModel property is renamed | Build breaks immediately — that's the point |\n\nThis gives you type-safe bindings with zero runtime reflection overhead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8dfb92d-bb6b-447e-9f56-2c15ff7819b2","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty and there are no files. The user is asking a general question about converting a MAUI page to use compiled bindings. I'll provide the answer directly since there's no existing code to modify.","outputTokens":752,"requestId":"044F:B86C3:A9EE1D:C26B8A:6A02796D"},"id":"5fd129b9-3a46-4729-8c89-51d24532ece6","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:09.366Z","parentId":"fb2fe63f-72c7-4cb1-85ec-e9539f345891"}
